Here is the right way to use:

```java
    //registry
    //zookeeper://127.0.0.1:2181
    referenceConfig.setRegistry("registryId"); // registryId is a reference of a RegistryConfig you defined locally or in Config Center.
    ......
```
or
```java
    //registry
    //zookeeper://127.0.0.1:2181
   RegistryConfig registryConfig = new RegistryConfig();
   registryConfig.setAddress("zookeeper://127.0.0.1:2181");
    referenceConfig.setRegistry(registryConfig);
    ......
```

Hi, @zhaixiaoxiang 

``` 
if (type == char.class || type == Character.class) {
    return value.length() > 0 ? value.charAt(0) : '\0';
}
```

Return '\0' may be confusing.

How about put the `if StringUtils.isRealBlank(value)` in the first line of this method?
But be careful if the '\0' is used in other place.

